snippet.textDisplay:
This song clearly stands on the shoulders of Rahat Fateh Ali Khan's vocals. With hardly any major musical interludes in the middle, every gap of the song is filled with Rahat sahab's magical notes. The second half of the song- "Mohe apne rang mein rang de Nizam" gradually moves towards a more classical based singing style where I could identify patterns which are used while singing a typical 'bandish'. 

What I really liked is the use of Shehnai, it adds another dimension to the music. The song becomes a wholesome experience with the qawali styled elements and beautiful backing vocals by the Humnawa group.

Overall a treat for all Rahat Fateh Ali Khan fans. His singing is so strong, it goes without saying. I always look forward to hear his detailed harkats, which are highlights in their own right.
